                                                                    




                                                                # DAY 3 GIT TRACKING AND FIRST COMMIT



1> Untracked file = An untracked file is a new file that git can see but is not tracking yet.


2> git add = git add tells git to start tracking the file and places it in the staging area.


3> staging area = staging area is a temporary area where files stay after git add and beforee git commit.


4> git commit = permanently saves the staged chnages as a new version or files in git history.



5> git log = show the  all saved commits(version) in git history.





                                                       
 
